OL,4,Craid
OL,6,FDuring a police interview he admitted
OL,7,Fhe was "off his face" on valium."
OL,9,FMiss Holmes said the the shopkeeper
OL,10,Fwas left "scared for his life."
OL,12,FShe said he was left with "more than
OL,13,Fminimal psychological effects".
OL,15,FMichael Forrest, defending, said his
OL,16,Fclient, who had 21 previous
OL,17,Fconvictions. had "fallen back into his
OL,18,Fold habits of taking valium" after a
OL,19,Flong spell of non-offending.
