OL,3,CMoment 'gunman' pulled trigger in shop
OL,4,Craid
OL,6,FHe said: "He still does not know why.
OL,7,FHe recognises the futility and the
OL,8,Fmadness of it. He questions what he
OL,9,Fwas trying to do. He was not thinking
OL,10,Fbeyond that he needed alcohol."
OL,12,FLetters in reference, were submitted
OL,13,Fon his behalf.
OL,15,FMr Forrest said: "He is deeply ashamed
OL,16,Fand embarrassed that his daughter has
OL,17,Fto come to see him in prison."
OL,19,FFinnie was jailed for four years and
OL,20,Fgiven a five-year restraining order.
